INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Chrysler|LHS', 'The Chrysler LHS primarily used the Sentry Key Immobilizer System (SKIS), requiring a transponder key and a 4-digit PIN for programming. The IMMO system is reliable and follows the same logic as the Concorde and 300M models of the late 90s and early 2000s. Key cutting is mechanical and straightforward for any locksmith with a standard machine. Watch for issues with the BCM, which can occasionally desync the transponder data if the vehicle has been jump-started improperly.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Chrysler|PT Cruiser', 'The Chrysler PT Cruiser uses the standard Sentry Key system (SKIM/SKREEM) throughout its production run, typically with the ID46 transponder. Programming is a simple 5-minute task through the OBDII port once the 4-digit security PIN is extracted. Most professional tools can pull the PIN directly from the car''s memory without needing to contact the dealer. Be careful when removing the column trim, as the plastic is often brittle and the transponder antenna ring is easily damaged.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Chrysler|Pacifica', 'The Chrysler Pacifica morphed from an early crossover using Sentry Keys to a modern minivan with advanced proximity ''Keyless Go'' systems. Modern proximity-equipped Pacificas (2017+) use the FIAT-based security architecture and require an SGW bypass or authorized server access for programming. Success rates are high once the gateway is bypassed, but the process requires precise timing for the proximity handshake. Always check for a ''Key Not Recognized'' error, which can often be solved by replacing the battery in the proximity fob.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Chrysler|Sebring', 'The Chrysler Sebring used a variety of security systems including standard Sentry Keys and later integrated Fobik keys. Convertible and Sedan versions share the same architecture, typically using the ID46 transponder or the 05129 style Fobik. Programming is straightforward via the OBDII port with a 4-digit PIN and standard Chrysler software. Watch for the ''Security'' light in the cluster; if it stays on, it usually indicates an incorrect key variant or a PIN that hasn''t been properly cleared.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Chrysler|Town & Country', 'The Chrysler Town & Country is the quintessential Fobik-key vehicle, utilizing the Winmodule (WCM) or Ignition Node (IGNM) systems. Programming these ''plastic keys'' is robust and usually works on the first try with professional locksmith software and a 4-digit PIN. Many models support remote start and power sliding door functions which are integrated into the main Fobik. pro tip: If the WCM/Ignition Node fails (key won''t turn), it may need a reset or replacement before any new keys can be programmed.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Chrysler|Voyager', 'The Chrysler Voyager uses the same security systems as the Town & Country, primarily focusing on Sentry Key transponders and later Fobik-style fobs. Programming follows the standard Chrysler routine via OBDII, requiring a 4-digit PIN for access to the immobilizer data. Key cutting is mechanical and straightforward, with high availability for aftermarket blanks. Success is usually guaranteed if the tech has a tool capable of PIN extraction and the correct 05129-style Fobik key.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Daewoo|Lanos', 'The Daewoo Lanos utilizes an early Daewoo-specific transponder system, often using an ID48 or similar fixed-code chip. It does not follow standard GM logic, so locksmiths must use tools that support ''Daewoo'' specific software to program the keys. The process is relatively simple once communication is established, but many generic tools lack the necessary protocols. Mechanically, the keys are simple double-sided cuts that are easy to replicate if a working key is present.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Daewoo|Leganza', 'The Daewoo Leganza features a transponder system that requires specialized Daewoo diagnostic software for key learning. It typically uses electronic chips that must be initialized to the immobilizer module via the OBDII port. Because these vehicles are increasingly rare, software support can be sparse on some newer multi-brand tools. pro tip: Check the immobilizer box location under the dashboard if communication fails, as wiring corrosion is a common issue with these older Korean platforms.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Daewoo|Nubira', 'The Daewoo Nubira uses a transponder-based security system that is consistent with the rest of the Daewoo lineup from the late 90s. Programming keys requires a tool with dedicated Daewoo coverage and often involves a handshake with the central control unit. Mechanical keys are standard profiles and are easily cut on basic equipment. Given the age, ensure the vehicle''s main battery is strong, as low voltage frequently causes ''failed communication'' errors during the transponder learn phase.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Avenger', 'The Dodge Avenger utilizes the Chrysler Sentry Key (SKREEM) system, featuring the standard ID46 transponder or the 05129 Fobik key depending on the generation. Programming is straightforward via the OBDII port and requires a 4-digit PIN for access. Success rates are high with professional tools that can automatically extract the security PIN. Watch for the ''Security'' light on the dash which can indicate an antenna ring failure, common in high-mileage Avengers.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Caliber', 'The Dodge Caliber features the Sentry Key system (SKIM/SKREEM) utilizing a transponder-integrated remote key. It requires a 4-digit PIN for programming, which most locksmith tools can pull directly through the diagnostic port. The process is very reliable and typically takes less than 10 minutes to complete. Be aware that the ''Wireless Control Module'' (WCM) on these models is known to lock up, which can prevent the car from starting or accepting new keys until reset.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Challenger', 'The Dodge Challenger uses Chrysler''s Fobik and advanced proximity systems, moving to the ''Powernet'' architecture in 2011+. Programming requires a 4-digit PIN and standard Chrysler proximity keys, which are well-supported by all major professional platforms. For 2018+ models, a Security Gateway Module (SGW) bypass is mandatory to allow any programming commands. pro tip: During ''All Keys Lost'' on modern proximity models, ensures the battery is fully charged to maintain communication with the central hub.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Charger', 'The Dodge Charger evolved from early Sentry Keys to Fobiks and modern proximity smart keys. Programming for 2011+ models focuses on the proximity architecture, requiring a 4-digit PIN and specific Chrysler fobs. 2018 and newer Chargers feature a Security Gateway that must be bypassed using an adapter or authorized tool access. If you encounter a ''Key Not Found'' message after programming, try the ''Emergency Start'' by pressing the fob directly against the Start/Stop button.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Dakota', 'The Dodge Dakota utilized the Sentry Key Immobilizer System throughout its later generations, typically using the ID46 transponder. Programming is a standard Chrysler procedure via the OBDII port, requiring a 4-digit PIN for security verification. Keys are generally integrated remote-head keys or simple transponders which are widely available in the aftermarket. Success is high, provided the locksmith has a tool capable of PIN extraction from the SKIM module.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Dart', 'The Dodge Dart is unique as it uses a FIAT-based security architecture, requiring different protocols than standard Dodge models. It utilizes proximity or high-security transponder keys that require a 4-digit PIN for any programming through the OBDII port. Most professional multi-brand tools handle this via a dedicated ''Dart/FIAT'' software module. Be careful when choosing keys, as the internal chip and remote frequency are specific to this model''s Italian-derived electronics.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Durango', 'The Dodge Durango features security ranging from early transponders to Fobiks and modern proximity keys. 2014+ models utilize a full proximity system that is programmed via OBDII once the 4-digit PIN is extracted. For 2018+ variants, an SGW bypass cable is necessary to communicate with the vehicle''s BCM for key learning. Always check the proximity transmitter pocket location in the center console if the car fails to detect a new key during the learn sequence.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Grand Caravan', 'The Dodge Grand Caravan is the quintessential Fobik-key vehicle, using the Winmodule (WCM) security platform. Programming is very reliable and is a core task for any automotive locksmith, requiring a 4-digit PIN and standard Chrysler Fobiks. The system supports multiple fobs including variants for remote start and power sliding doors. If the ignition won''t turn, the Winmodule itself may be faulty, a common issue on high-use commercial and family vans.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Journey', 'The Dodge Journey utilizes either Fobik keys or proximity smart keys depending on the trim and model year. Programming for both is standard via the OBDII port, but proximity models (2011+) require a specific learn sequence and 4-digit PIN. For 2018+ Journeys, verify if an SGW bypass is needed, as it was rolled out mid-cycle on some production lines. Watch for the ''Starting System Fault'' which can be caused by a desynced key or a failing RFHM module.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Magnum', 'The Dodge Magnum features the Chrysler Sentry Key or early Fobik systems, utilizing a 4-digit PIN for all programming activities. It is well-supported by all professional diagnostic tools, with PIN extraction usually taking less than a minute. Key profiles are standard Chrysler laser-cut or double-sided depending on the year. pro tip: If the remote fobs won''t program, check the diversity antenna in the rear window, which is a common failure point that affects remote range.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Neon', 'The Dodge Neon utilized the early Sentry Key Immobilizer System (SKIS), featuring simple transponder keys with ID46 or earlier chips. Programming is easily accomplished via the OBDII port using a 4-digit PIN and basic Chrysler software. Mechanically, the keys are standard Chrysler M-series cuts that are easy to duplicate. Keep an eye on the SKIM module (immobilizer), as it can occasionally drop its memory if the vehicle experiences chronic low voltage issues.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Nitro', 'The Dodge Nitro uses the Sentry Key (SKREEM) system, typically featuring a 4-button integrated remote key with an ID46 transponder. Programming follows the standard Chrysler routine, requiring a 4-digit PIN that is easily pulled through the OBDII port. The process is very reliable and usually completed in under 10 minutes. Note that the Nitro''s door locks are prone to mechanical failure, making Lishi decoding a valuable skill for ''All Keys Lost'' on this model.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|RAM', 'The Dodge RAM (and newer RAM Trucks) utilizes security platforms ranging from ''Circle Plus'' transponders to Fobiks and modern proximities. Modern RAM proximity systems (2013+) are programmed via OBDII and require a 4-digit PIN for access. Since 2018, RAM trucks have high-security gateways that must be bypassed with a ''CABLE'' or authorized tool to allow ANY key programming. Always verify if the truck is a ''Classic'' or ''DT'' body style, as they use different key fobs and communication protocols.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Ram Promaster', 'The Ram Promaster is based on a FIAT platform and uses a completely different security architecture than standard Dodge trucks. It utilizes high-security laser-cut keys with ID46 transponders that require a 5-digit FIAT PIN code for programming. Most professional tools handle this via the ''Fiat/Iveco'' software modules rather than the Chrysler menu. Success depends on obtaining the correct PIN and using high-quality transponder keys that are specifically compatible with the Promaster BCM.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Sprinter', 'The Dodge Sprinter is a rebadged Mercedes-Benz and uses a specialized Mercedes-based transponder system (typically FBS2/FBS3). Programming requires specialized Mercedes tools and reading the SKREEM or EIS module directly, as standard Chrysler tools will NOT work. Keys are high-security laser-cut profiles that must be accurately prepared before they can be learned to the car. This is a technical job that usually requires an EEPROM pull or high-end bench-top programming equipment.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Stratus', 'The Dodge Stratus used two distinct security platforms: Chrysler-based for sedans and Mitsubishi-based for coupes. Sedans are programmed via the standard Chrysler Sentry Key routine (ID46 + 4-digit PIN), while Coupes require Mitsubishi software and PINs. Always check the first digit of the VIN to determine the origin (1-5 for Chrysler, J for Mitsubishi). This distinction is critical for selecting the correct key blank and programming protocol for a successful job.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Dodge|Viper', 'The Dodge Viper uses high-security transponder or proximity systems depending on the generation, with newer models sharing FCA''s proximity architecture. Programming is a sensitive process that requires a 4-digit PIN and professional tools with specific Viper software support. Given the limited production, ensure your tool is fully updated before attempting to program a new key. pro tip: Always use a battery maintainer, as the Viper''s performance-oriented electronics are sensitive to the voltage fluctuations common during a security handshake.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Fiat|124 Spider', 'The Fiat 124 Spider (based on the Mazda ND platform) uses a Mazda-derived proximity security system. Keys are proximity-based and programmed using standard Mazda 20-digit or 12-digit PIN extraction procedures through the OBDII port. Most professional multi-brand tools handle this easily via the ''Mazda/Fiat'' software selection. It is a very reliable system, but ensure you have the correct ''Mazda-style'' proximity fob for successful pairing.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Fiat|500', 'The Fiat 500 utilizes the ''Fiat Code'' system, featuring high-security laser-cut keys with ID46 or similar transponder chips. Programming requires a 5-digit PIN code which can be extracted from the BCM using advanced locksmith tools. The process usually involves a pre-coding step where the key is initialized with vehicle-specific data before being learned via OBDII. Success depends on using high-quality keys, as generic chips often fail to authenticate with the Fiat immobilizer.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Fiat|500L', 'The Fiat 500L shares its security architecture with the larger Fiat and Jeep Renegade models, utilizing an FCA-based BCM. Programming requires a 5-digit PIN and advanced tools capable of ''Fiat'' or ''Chrysler/Jeep'' proximity/key learning. On 2018+ models, ensure you have an SGW bypass cable ready, as the security gateway will block any unauthorized OBDII communication. The process is straightforward once the gateway is cleared and the correct PIN is entered.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Fiat|500x', 'The Fiat 500x uses the same platform as the Jeep Renegade and features a modern proximity security architecture. It typically utilizes proximity smart keys that require a 5-digit PIN for programming through the diagnostic port. For models built after 2018, a Security Gateway (SGW) bypass is mandatory to allow key learning commands. Always check for ''Service Antitheft'' messages, which can indicate an antenna or BCM handshake issue during the programming process.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Bronco', 'The Ford Bronco spans classic mechanical systems to the modern 2021+ ''Fortress'' security architecture. Modern Broncos utilize proximity smart keys with 128-bit encryption that are programmed via the OBDII port on most professional locksmith platforms. For ''All Keys Lost'' on newer models, there may be a 10-minute security wait or a requirement for authorized server access. pro tip: On the 2021+ models, the proximity transmitter pocket is located in the center console under the rubber mat.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|C-Max', 'The Ford C-Max utilizes the Ford ''PATS'' (Passive Anti-Theft System) and proximity smart key architectures. Programming is generally very efficient through the OBDII port, requiring two keys for a full ''All Keys Lost'' reset on most model years. If you encounter a ''security access denied'' error, verify that the vehicle battery is fully charged, as Fords are highly sensitive to voltage drops during key learning. Proximity keys for the C-Max are well-supported by Autel and Lonsdor tools.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Crown Victoria', 'The Ford Crown Victoria is a locksmith staple, utilizing the early PATS system with an 80-bit transponder (often ID63). Programming is straightforward via the OBDII port, traditionally requiring a 10-minute security wait for ''All Keys Lost'' access. The mechanical keys are standard Ford 8-cut profiles which are extremely easy to duplicate or originate using a Lishi tool. Be aware that most Police Interceptor models do NOT have a transponder system, but always check for the security light to be sure.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|E-Series Van', 'The Ford E-Series (Econoline) utilize the standard PATS transponder system for most years after 1998. Programming is a 10-minute OBDII task with any professional locksmith tool, featuring a very high success rate. The mechanical door and ignition locks are prone to wear in commercial use, making ''key sticking'' a common complaint that requires mechanical servicing. Most E-Series keys are simple transponder-integrated heads that are very affordable and durable for fleet use.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Edge', 'The Ford Edge has transitioned from standard transponder keys to advanced proximity smart key systems across its generations. Key programming is standard Ford OBDII procedure, requiring either two keys for a reset or a single key bypass on some newer tools. For proximity models, the ''transmitter pocket'' is usually found in the center console or on the steering column. Success is generally high, but always check if the vehicle has the ''MyKey'' restriction active, which can limit the functions of the new key.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Escape', 'The Ford Escape is a high-volume vehicle with security evolving from early PATS (ID60/ID63) to modern push-button start systems. Most models are easily programmed via OBDII in minutes, with ''All Keys Lost'' typically requiring a 10-minute wait or a ''direct access'' tool. 2020+ models use Ford''s latest encrypted proximity architecture, which is well-supported but requires an active internet connection on some tool platforms. Watch for the ''Starting System Fault'' message, which often indicates a failed transponder handshake.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Excursion', 'The Ford Excursion utilizes the early PATS system, featuring transponder-integrated keys that are easily matched to the vehicle via OBDII. Like the F-250 and Super Duty models of its era, it requires a 10-minute security wait for ''All Keys Lost'' access. The mechanical locks are standard Ford 8-cut profiles, frequently found with heavy wear due to the age of the vehicle. Most locksmiths can originate or clone these keys in under 15 minutes with standard diagnostic and cutting equipment.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Expedition', 'The Ford Expedition features robust security spanning from standard PATS transponders to modern 2018+ proximity architectures. Programming is standard via the OBDII port, with newer proximity models typically using the center console transmitter pocket for learning. For 2018 and newer Expeditions, ensure your tool has the latest Ford software to handle the newer encryption layers and data gateway. Always verify if the vehicle has ''intelligent access'' fobs (proximity) or ''standard fobs with a flip-key'' as they require different programming flows.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Explorer', 'The Ford Explorer is one of the most common vehicles for key programming, utilizing multiple generations of PATS and modern proximity systems. Most professional tools offer a 10-minute bypass for security access, making ''All Keys Lost'' very efficient for the technician. On 2011+ proximity models, if the car doesn''t respond to the new key, check thetransmitter pocket located in the center console under the tray. Note: 2020+ models use the latest Ford security architecture and may require an online server token for full access.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|F-150', 'The Ford F-150 is the most popular vehicle in North America and a core job for locksmiths, ranging from early transponders to the 2021+ ''Fortress'' architecture. Modern F-150s (2021+) require advanced tools with the latest 128-bit encryption support for proximity key learning. For older models, two keys are often required to complete a security reset, though most professional tools can bypass this requirement. pro tip: On 2015-2020 proximity models, the transmitter pocket is located under the rubber mat at the bottom of the front cup holders.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|F250 - F750', 'Ford Super Duty trucks utilize the standard PATS or modern proximity security systems, with many fleet models using simple transponder keys. Programming is very reliable via OBDII, typically taking about 10 minutes to complete the security access wait. The mechanical locks are robust but can seize in dusty or salt-heavy environments, so lubrication is often needed during the job. Success rates are extremely high across all professional locksmith platforms for these heavy-duty workhorses.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Fiesta', 'The Ford Fiesta uses both standard transponder keys and optional proximity smart keys, typically using the ID83 or similar chips. Programming is straightforward via the OBDII port and usually supports a 10-minute security bypass for faster turnarounds. If you are working on a proximity model, the ''emergency'' start location is on the steering column shroud where the ignition cylinder would normally be. Watch for ''Low Battery'' warnings, which are very common on the Fiesta and can interrupt the key learning process.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Five Hundred', 'The Ford Five Hundred utilized the PATS system with an 80-bit transponder chip, consistent with the Taurus models of its era. Programming is an OBDII task that requires a 10-minute security wait for ''All Keys Lost'' access or an immediate addition for spare keys. The mechanical keys are standard Ford 8-cut profiles, easily handled by any high-security or basic cutter. Be aware that the BCM on these models can occasionally desync if the battery is depleted during a key learning attempt.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Flex', 'The Ford Flex features either high-security transponder keys or proximity smart keys depending on the configuration. Programming for both follows the standard Ford OBDII flow, with proximity models using the center console transmitter pocket for sync. Success is high on tools like the Autel IM608 or VVDI2, which offer broad coverage for the Flex''s production run. If the remote functions don''t work, ensure you are using the correct FCC ID, as there are several fobs that look identical but have different frequencies.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Focus', 'The Ford Focus has a broad range of security tech, from early ID60 transponders on the ZX3 to advanced proximity keys on newer hatchbacks. Programming is well-supported via the OBDII port, with ''All Keys Lost'' on most models taking about 10 minutes for security initialization. On 2012+ proximity models, if the car won''t wake up, use the emergency start slot on the steering column. pro tip: Focus ignition cylinders are famous for binding; if the key won''t turn, it''s likely a mechanical failure rather than an electronic one.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Fusion', 'The Ford Fusion is another high-volume locksmith job, moving from early transponders to the widely used high-security flip-keys and proximity smart fobs. Modern Fusions (2013+) are easily programmed via OBDII in about 10 minutes using most professional diagnostic tools. For models with ''All Keys Lost,'' ensure you have two keys ready as several years require a minimum of two fobs to complete the learn cycle. Check the transmission position; many Fusions will not allow key programming if the car isn''t strictly in ''Park''.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Maverick', 'The modern Ford Maverick utilizes Ford''s latest 128-bit proximity security architecture and is standard with push-button start or high-security fobs. Programming is performed through the OBDII port and usually requires an active internet connection on your tool for the latest security handshake. The transmitter pocket for proximity keys is typically located in the center console storage area. As a new model, success requires your programming tool to be updated with the 2022+ Ford software modules.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Mustang', 'The Ford Mustang is an icon that has used everything from early PATS (ID60) to advanced 2015+ proximity and the latest 2024+ architectures. For 2015-2023 models, proximity keys are easily added via the center console transmitter pocket (located under the cup holder rubber). 2024+ ''S650'' Mustangs feature enhanced security that may require authorized server access on some professional tools. Always check for the ''Security'' light; if it flashes rapidly, the transponder or proximity chip is not being recognized by the immobilizer cluster.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Mustang Mach-E', 'The Ford Mustang Mach-E uses Ford''s most advanced EV security architecture, strictly utilizing proximity smart keys and ''Phone as a Key'' (PaaK) technology. Programming new fobs requires high-end tools with the latest Ford 2021+ software and usually an active internet connection for the ''Fortress'' security verification. The transmitter pocket is located in the center console. Because it is a high-tech EV, always ensure the 12V system is backed up during the programming sequence to avoid module communication errors.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Ranger', 'The Ford Ranger spans early PATS systems (ID63) in the classic trucks to the modern 2019+ proximity architecture in the reborn models. Classic Rangers are very easy to program via OBDII in 10 minutes, while newer models follow the modern Ford proximity flow. In ''All Keys Lost'' for 2019+ Rangers, the process is streamlined on tools like the IM608, generally taking less than 15 minutes. Watch for worn door locks on older Rangers, which can make Lishi decoding a challenge due to excessive mechanical play.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Taurus', 'The Ford Taurus features multiple generations of security, culminating in the high-security proximity and flip-key systems of the later 2010s models. Programming is standard via the OBDII port, with a 10-minute security wait commonly required for full access. For proximity-equipped cars, the key must be placed in the designated transmitter pocket in the center console for active sync. If you encounter a ''Key Not Detected'' error, try a hard battery reset which can clear the central gateway''s buffer on these models.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Transit', 'The Ford Transit full-size van utilitizes Ford''s modern security architectures, primarily using high-security flip-keys or proximity smart keys. Programming is an OBDII task that is very stable on professional platforms like the IM608 and VVDI2. Given the commercial nature, ''All Keys Lost'' is a common job, requiring about 10 minutes for security clearance. pro tip: The Transit''s mechanical door locks are high-security ''tibbe'' or ''laser-cut'' depending on the year; ensure you have the correct cutting equipment before arriving on-site.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Ford|Transit Connect', 'The Ford Transit Connect utilizes high-security transponder or flip-keys consistent with the European Ford platform architecture (ID63 or Hitag). Programming is straightforward through the OBDII port with a 10-minute security wait for ''All Keys Lost'' situations. Most locksmiths find these vans to be very reliable for key learning with high success rates in under 15 minutes. Note that the mechanical ignition is prone to wear, so if the key won''t rotate, check for a mechanical wafer collapse before assuming it is an electronic fault.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('GMC|Acadia', 'The GMC Acadia uses the GM Global-A proximity security architecture for most of its production run, featuring Hitag 3 or ID46 transponders. Programming is standard via the OBDII port and usually takes about 12 minutes to complete the security learn sequence. For proximity models, the transmitter pocket is located in the center console; placing the key there is essential for successful recognition. Note that newer 2023+ models move to the highly secure Global-B platform requiring CAN-FD hardware.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('GMC|Canyon', 'The GMC Canyon utilizes the GM ''Circle Plus'' transponder system or the modern Global-A platform depending on the generation. It uses traditional transponder keys with ID46 chips or high-security flip-keys that are easily programmed via OBDII in minutes. Most locksmiths can perform a key addition or ''All Keys Lost'' through a standard 10-minute routine. Note that 2023+ models move to the Global-B architecture, requiring CAN-FD hardware and professional-grade security access.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('GMC|Envoy', 'The GMC Envoy features the GM Passlock II or ''Circle Plus'' transponder systems, depending on the production year. Programming for transponder-equipped models is reliable via the OBDII port once the 10-minute security wait is completed. The mechanical ignition cylinders are a common failure point; if the key won''t turn, it''s often a mechanical wafer issue rather than an electronic fault. pro tip: Check the BCM in the passenger footwell for water damage if you encounter chronic communication issues on older Envoys.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('GMC|Savana', 'The GMC Savana full-size van utilitizes the standard GM transponder system, evolving from early Passlock to ''Circle Plus'' (PK3+) and current encrypted variants. This is a very robust system for locksmiths, with key additions taking less than 10 minutes in most cases through the OBDII port. The mechanical keys are standard GM 6-cut or 10-cut profiles and are usually very easy to duplicate. success is high, provided the tech has a tool capable of handling GM''s standard security routines.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('GMC|Sierra', 'The GMC Sierra features security ranging from ''Circle Plus'' transponders to the most advanced CAN-FD Global-B proximity systems. Newer models (2022+ Refreshed models) require CAN-FD adapters and often authorized server tokens for any key-related work. Older ''Circle Plus'' (2007-2013) models are extremely common and easy to program in minutes via OBDII. pro tip: On modern Sierras, the transmitter pocket location can vary, so check the center console tray or the cup holder if the key isn''t detected initially.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('GMC|Terrain', 'The GMC Terrain uses the GM Global-A security platform, featuring high-security flip-keys or proximity smart keys. It utilizes Hitag 3 or ID46 transponder chips that are easily programmable through the OBDII port in about 12 minutes. The system is very consistent across all years, though 2023+ models are likely moving to the more secure Global-B platform. Always verify if the vehicle has a ''Keyed'' ignition or ''Push Button Start'' as they require different programming flows.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('GMC|Yukon', 'The GMC Yukon uses the same high-security platforms as the Sierra, moving from ''Circle Plus'' to Global-A and modern Global-B proximity systems. Global-B models (2021+) require CAN-FD hardware and often an active connection to GM''s security database for authorized programming. Older ''Circle Plus'' systems are straightforward and can be handled in under 10 minutes by most technicians. pro tip: In proximity-equipped Yukons, the transmitter pocket is often located in the center console or underneath the cup holder liners.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Genesis|G70', 'The Genesis G70 utilizes the Hyundai/Kia modern proximity smart key architecture, featuring 47 or 8A-AES encrypted transponders. Programming is a standard proximity learn process via the OBDII port, requiring a 6-digit PIN code extracted from the BCM or VIN. Major professional tools offer excellent coverage and typically complete the process in under 10 minutes. Always check for the ''Key Not Detected'' error, which can often be solved by placing the key directly against the Start/Stop button during the handshake.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Genesis|G80', 'The Genesis G80 features a sophisticated proximity-based security system consistent with high-trim Hyundai luxury vehicles. It uses smart keys that are easily added through the OBDII port once the correct 6-digit security PIN is obtained. The process is quick and reliable, provided the locksmith has an active tool with current Hyundai/Genesis software. if you encounter a ''Learn Failed'' message, perform a full module scan to ensure no existing communication faults are blocking the security gateway.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Genesis|G90', 'As the flagship model, the Genesis G90 uses the most advanced implementation of the Hyundai/Kia smart key architecture, featuring high-level proximity encryption. Programming requires a 6-digit PIN and professional tools with specific Genesis luxury-tier software updates. The process involves a multi-stage sync between the smart key unit and the central gateway to authorize the new key. Given the complexity, ensure the battery voltage is strictly maintained throughout the programming procedure to prevent data corruption.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Genesis|GV60', 'The Genesis GV60 electric vehicle utilizes the modern E-GMP proximity security platform, featuring high-precision smart keys and digital key capabilities. Programming is performed through the OBDII port and requires the latest 2022+ software updates on your locksmith tool. Because it is an EV, always be mindful of the 12V battery health during the proximity learn sequence, as low voltage can cause authentication failures. The transmitter pocket for proximity keys is generally located in the center console area.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Genesis|GV70', 'The Genesis GV70 uses the latest proximity smart key technology from the Hyundai/Kia group, often featuring integrated remote start and parking assist commands. Programming requires a 6-digit PIN and an OBDII learn routine that is well-supported by high-end locksmith tools like the IM608. Success rates are high, but ensure you have the correct FCC ID smart key as several Genesis variants look identical but are electronically incompatible. Always verify that all proximity functions work correctly before finishing the job.', '2026-02-05');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO vehicle_descriptions (vehicle_key, description, generated) VALUES ('Genesis|GV80', 'The Genesis GV80 features the premium proximity architecture found across the Genesis luxury SUV line, requiring high-security smart keys. Programming is a standard 10-minute OBDII procedure once the 6-digit PIN is extracted or provided. Professional tools provide reliable access to the BCM for key initialization, but 2023+ models may have updated encryption layers. pro tip: If the car fails to recognize the new key, hold the key fob directly against the Start/Stop button for 5 seconds to initiate the emergency'' induction sync.', '2026-02-05');
